Usage

Option 1: Local dev (recommended for daily work)
Run just the database in Docker, Next.js natively:
# Start Postgres
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d

# Run Next.js with hot reload
pnpm dev
Database URL: postgresql://thurman:thurman@localhost:5432/thurman

Option 2: Full containerized stack
Build and run everything in Docker:
# Build and start
docker compose up --build
# Or in background
docker compose up --build -d
Then open http://localhost:3000

Useful commands
# Stop everything
docker compose down
# Stop and wipe database
docker compose down -v
# View logs
docker compose logs -f web
# Shell into database
docker exec -it thurman-db psql -U thurman -d thurman

Before first run with Prisma
After starting the database, run migrations:
cd packages/db
cp example.env .env  # Set DATABASE_URL=postgresql://thurman:thurman@localhost:5432/thurman
pnpm db:push         # Push schema to database
